In almost all zones (planer too) when I ToT mobs I typically get back 3/4 to a full blue of mana back into my system (lvl 57 with about 3k mana total).<P>However in Ssraeshza Temple when I ToT I get back 1/8th to almost no noticable mana at all and that is at the outset of the fights.  It's one of the only spells I can land at the get-go and not get aggro at my level (or any level probably).<P>Are the mobs there simply not filled with mana (even thou they CH themselves a lot) or can a mob "partially" resist ToT?<P>Thanks.
