We've known for quite a while that Wandering Mind gives mana to the target instead of taking, thanks to the folks on the PvP servers.  But it looks like it's a bit more bugged than that.<P>Last night, my DSL went down right as I was pulling in the Deep.  So I died.  Today, I CR'd using myself and my paladin.  Thinking to regain mana back faster after the ress, I memmed ToT and Wandering Mind.  Sooner I get full mana, sooner I can start pulling, right?  So I dueled and buffed and medded and the like.<P>And then I figured, hey, since it's just me and me and I'm not using anything AE and I can still heal myself, if I ditch root on Ax for Wandering Mind, that's more mana for both Ax and my paladin.  So I didn't end the duel by zoning and started to pull.<P>But surprise surprise... Ax's mana seemed to regen slower than ever.  So after recovering some of my lost xp, I decided to experiment a little.  I clicked off C2 and GoB, leaving just my natural regen and MC2.  I drained myself of mana.  <P>I then cast Wandering Mind whenever it refreshed upon my paladin and sat the rest of the time.  After ten minutes, I'd regained 2.8 bubs of mana.<P>Then I drained myself again and just sat.  In 10 more minutes, I regained 3.9 bubs of mana.<P>Based upon that, I'm gonna state that Wandering Mind is completely reversed.  It not only boosts the mana regen of the target, it lowers ours.<P>Anyone want to do some testing of their own to verify my findings?
<br />&nbsp;
